data.text:
2022-23 - Sun Belt Conference Academic Commissioner’s List

2021-22 - Sun Belt Conference Academic Commissioner’s List

2023-24: Played in two games … Was on the field for 49 total snaps (42 offense, seven special teams) … Played 40 snaps on offense in the opener against The Citadel … Was on the field for 10 snaps in the win over UAB … Suffered a broken right leg and had surgery … Missed the rest of the season … Made the Dean’s List in the spring for posting a GPA higher than 3.50.

2022-23: Played in all 13 games … Was on the field for 86 total snaps (12 offense, 74 special teams) … Played 11 snaps on offense and eight on special teams in the opener against Morgan State … Saw action on special teams in the win at Nebraska and at UAB … Played special teams against Ball State and against Coastal Carolina … Was on the field for six special teams snaps at Georgia State and eight in the win over No. 25 James Madison … Played five snaps on special teams in the win at Old Dominion and six against South Alabama … Was on the field for four special teams snaps at Louisiana and two against Marshall … Played nine total snaps in the overtime win over App State … Played three snaps on special teams in the Camellia Bowl against Buffalo … Made the Honor Roll in the fall … Made the Dean’s List in the spring for earning a 3.50 GPA or higher.

2021-22: Played in two games and was able to redshirt … Played 12 total snaps on offense … Made his collegiate debut against Arkansas State, playing eight offensive snaps … Played seven snaps on offense against South Alabama … Made the Dean’s List in the fall for posting a GPA higher than 3.50 … … Made the President’s List in the spring for making a perfect 4.00 GPA.

2020-21: Graduated from high school early and enrolled at Georgia Southern in January … Went through spring practice with the Eagles … Made the President’s List in the spring for posting a perfect 4.0 GPA.

HIGH SCHOOL: Played at Brunswick High for Coach Sean Pender … A first-team all-state selection for the 6A level by the Atlanta Journal-Constitution … Ranked the No. 102 offensive guard in the country by 247Sports … Rated as the No. 122 offensive guard in the country by ESPN.com … Named all-state, all-region and All-Coastal Area as a junior … Also participated in track & field.

PERSONAL: Born Caleb Cook on October 3 in Brunswick, GA … Son of Cathy Chastine and Gary Cook.

MAJOR: Multimedia Journalism/Communications (double major)
